{{Infobox book | italic title = <!--(see above)--> | name = Enemy at the gates : the battle for Stalingrad | image = Enemy at the Gates The Battle for Stalingrad.jpg| image_size = | alt = | caption = | author = | subject = [[Battle of Stalingrad]] during World War II | genre = history | publisher = | publisher2 = | pub_date = | english_pub_date = | media_type = | pages = xvii, 457 pages | awards = | isbn = 0141390174 | oclc = 613817 | dewey = | congress = }}
'''''Enemy at the Gates: The Battle for Stalingrad''''' is a book written by [[William Craig (author)|William Craig]] and published in 1973 by [[Reader's Digest Press]] and in 1974 by [[Penguin Publishing]]. The 2001 film ''[[Enemy at the Gates]]'' utilized the book's title and used it as one of its sources, but was not a direct adaptation of the work.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.epilog.de/Film/Dr_Dz/Texte/Duell_Enemy_at_the_Gates_USA_D_2001_Interview.htm| website=Epilog.de| title=Interview with Jean-Jacques Annaud, referenced by Constantin Film| language=German| deadurl=yes| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070818113711/http://www.epilog.de/Film/Dr_Dz/Texte/Duell_Enemy_at_the_Gates_USA_D_2001_Interview.htm| archivedate=2007-08-18| df=}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://articles.baltimoresun.com/2001-03-16/features/0103160144_1_vassili-zaitsev-danilov-jude-law|title=`Enemy at the Gates' is right on target|website=Baltimore Sun|access-date=2016-03-11}}</ref>
== Reception == The ''[[Slavic Review]]'' panned ''Enemy at the Gates'', calling it "rambling and exaggerated" and negatively comparing Craig to author [[Paul Carell]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Parrish|first=Michael|date=1974-01-01|title=Review of Enemy at the Gates: The Battle for Stalingrad|jstor=2495819|journal=Slavic Review|volume=33|issue=2|pages=363–364|doi=10.2307/2495819}}</ref> In contrast, ''[[The Washington Post]]'' was more favorable and drew favorable comparisons to [[Cornelius Ryan]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Ambrose|first1=Stephen E.|title=So much for so little|work=The Washington Post|date=04/08/1973}}</ref>
