'''''The Great War Symphony''''' is an upcoming work by the British composer [[Patrick Hawes]] due to be premiered in 2018.
It is a choral symphony in four movements with each movement depicting a year of the First World War.
The complete work will be premiered in 2018 as part of the World War I commemorations to mark the end of the centenary and will involve community choirs and musicians from across the UK.<ref>{{cite journal |last=Hewett |first=Ivan |title=The Great War Symphony: how music can honour the fallen |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group]] |date=20 April 2015 |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/classicalmusic/11545180/The-Great-War-Symphony-how-music-can-honour-the-fallen.html |accessdate=February 6, 2016}}</ref>
